Company: Ohio University College of Osteopathic Medicine
Description of incident: A clerical error led to the online            posting of the names and Social Security numbers of people who spoke            at Ohio University's Centers for Osteopathic Research and Education.            A spreadsheet that contained the information had been accessible since            March 20 and was discovered when a nurse found the information last            week while conducting online research. In addition to names and Social            Security numbers, the spreadsheet included contact numbers, addresses,            their speaking topics and federal employer identification numbers.
